the final report found that the pilot-in-command , who has been arrested and charged over the crash , attempted to land after fifteen Ground Proximity Warning System activations to tell him he was landing too fast , and says that although a longer runway and full-sized RESA would n 't have stopped an airliner traveling at such excessive speed it could have reduced the toll of deaths and injuries .
