Amnesty International ' s 2004 annual report on US human rights in 2003 agrees with many of these claims .
Amnesty is also worried about : severe violations committed by the United States ' army outside the countries ' borders ; the situation of the prisoners in Guantanamo Bay ; United States ' general misbehavior against international peace ; ill-treatment of US immigrants ; ill-treatment and excessive use of force by the US law enforcement officials ; the US citizens losing civil rights and liberties after the 9 / 11 attacks ; and continued use of death penalty by the state , which is in direct breach with the 3rd article of the United Nations ' Universal Declaration of Human Rights -LRB- the right to life -RRB- .
comment by Peter Edidin of The New York Times , characterized the Chinese report as `` a frank indictment [ that ] draws a picture of America that approaches caricature .
but that does n 't mean it wo n 't buttress the negative image of the United States held by its critics around the world . ' '
this ongoing dispute does not capture the entire relationship of US and China on civil rights .
